Sep 17 2008	A Good Value For A Centrally-Located Apartment	We have stayed at the Chelsea Towers several times. I would not consider it a full-service hotel, but rather an apartment-hotel with some front desk assistance. The apartments are comfortably furnished and spacious (try to get one higher up for a very nice view of the city &amp; gulf) but not overly ritzy. It is very convenient for a family or friends traveling together.We do have a baby, and the tile floor was not particularly suitable for her.The pool area is very nice and has plenty of shelter from sun/wind.The location to all of Dubai is excellent, as it is centrally located. Dubai has world-class traffic, so location is everything. There are a small variety of acceptable restaurants within walking distance.Big tip: if you need a taxi for a specific time (or a large taxi), come downstairs early - don't just call down &amp; order one! It will likely not be there when you come down. Don't expect full service here - just expect plenty of elbow room and a good location. Dubai hotels are VERY EXPENSIVE, and we have found this a suitable choice.	
